{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 11:34:23.729011", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary of the topology\n- Super-spine AS 65000 connects to two spines: spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) and spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101).\n- Each spine connects to both leaves in the pod: leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) and leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201).\n- Each leaf connects to a host and advertises 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24 via EBGP:\n  - pc_0_0 at 10.0.0.2 behind leaf_router_0_0 (10.0.0.0/24)\n  - pc_0_1 at 10.0.1.2 behind leaf_router_0_1 (10.0.1.0/24)\n- Inter-router links use 172.16.0.0/16 /31s consistent with the wiring.\n\nEnd-to-end data plane health\n- Host-to-host reachability:\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: 0% loss, RTT avg ~1.95 ms\n  - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0: 0% loss, RTT avg ~3.59 ms\n- Conclusion: End-to-end connectivity between hosts is healthy with low latency and no loss.\n\nControl plane (BGP) health\n- All EBGP sessions are established and exchanging routes:\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 2 peers (spines 65100, 65101), each advertising 1 prefix; router advertises 2.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 2 peers (spines 65100, 65101), each advertising 1 prefix; router advertises 2.\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100): 3 peers (super-spine 65000, leaves 65200/65201). Receives 1 prefix from each leaf, 0 from super-spine (expected; see notes below).\n  - spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): 3 peers (super-spine 65000, leaves 65200/65201). Receives 2 prefixes from super-spine, and 1 from each leaf.\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): 2 peers (spines 65100/65101). Receives 2 prefixes from each spine.\n- No signs of session flaps in the brief intervals observed; all sessions are in Established state.\n\nRouting state (selected findings)\n- leaf_router_0_0 RIB/FIB:\n  - Connected: 10.0.0.0/24 on host-facing interface.\n  - BGP: 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4 (spine 65100).\n- leaf_router_0_1 RIB/FIB:\n  - Connected: 10.0.1.0/24 on host-facing interface.\n  - BGP: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6 (spine 65100).\n- spine_router_0_0 RIB/FIB:\n  - BGP: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.5 (leaf 65200), 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.7 (leaf 65201).\n- spine_router_0_1 RIB/FIB:\n  - BGP: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.9 (leaf 65200), 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.11 (leaf 65201).\n- super_spine_router_0 RIB/FIB:\n  - BGP: 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 both installed via 172.16.0.1 (spine 65100).\n\nObservations and interpretation\n- End-to-end connectivity is fully functional with normal latency and zero packet loss.\n- BGP adjacencies are correctly formed across all layers; leaves are advertising their /24s, spines are learning both leaf prefixes, and super-spine is learning both prefixes from both spines.\n- The super-spine has selected a single best path (via spine 65100) for both /24s; ECMP is not active at the super-spine.\n- Leaves each receive the remote /24 from both spines (PfxRcd=1 from each), but only one path is installed in the FIB; ECMP is not active at the leaves.\n- Asymmetry in PfxRcd from the super-spine to the spines is expected:\n  - spine_router_0_0 shows 0 prefixes received from the super-spine because the super-spine’s chosen best paths come from spine_router_0_0; by default a route learned from a neighbor is not advertised back to that same neighbor, so no prefixes are received from the super-spine on spine_router_0_0. Conversely, spine_router_0_1 does receive 2 prefixes from the super-spine. This is normal behavior given best-path selection at the super-spine.\n\nAnomalies detected\n- None impacting reachability or stability.\n- Noteworthy but non-fatal: Lack of ECMP at the leaves and super-spine. In Clos designs, ECMP is typically desired for load-sharing and resilience; here only a single best path is installed at each device. This appears to be a configuration choice rather than a fault.\n\nFault localization and root cause\n- No faulty devices identified.\n- No control-plane or data-plane failures observed.\n- Root cause: Not applicable; the network is operating normally. The single-path selection (no ECMP) is a configuration characteristic, not a failure.\n\nOverall assessment\n- Network health: Good. All intended prefixes are advertised and reachable; host-to-host connectivity is normal; BGP sessions are stable.\n- No corrective action required from a fault perspective.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5802, "output_tokens": 4507, "total_tokens": 10309, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 3072}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3200}}}
